<recipe>
	<name>Sweet Chili Dipping Sauce</name>
	<notes>I'm a big fan of sweet chili sauce, though sadly not a big fan of the sodium content in some of the prepared ones.  I don't know if this is going to end up being a placeholder or what:  the amount of fish sauce contains about a day's worth of sodium, so my mileage may vary.

Plus, thi is one of those world-sufficiency things and I don't know that fish sauce is going to make it into my "ten ingredients" bag.</notes>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/3 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>rice wine vinegar</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2 Tbl</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>fish sauce</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/4 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>hot water</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2 Tbl</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>sugar</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>lime</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>juiced</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>minced garlic</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>red chili paste</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<preparation>Puree ingredients together and serve.</preparation>
